<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-05-29T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-05-29T00:00:00-05:00" n="618" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d618">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 422.11 G93/480.]</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Chargé
                                    d’Affaires</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Quito</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-05-29">
                                    <hi rend="italic">May 29, 1912</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Railway company controller now has draft of Minister of Hacienda for
                            57,230 sucres. The Minister has instructed Amsinck to pay railway
                            company through Consul General, New York, 28,770 sucres. Controller has
                            draft on said Consul General 14,000 sucres. Total, 100,000.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Bingham</hi>.</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>